I find that a good visual graphic is very useful for public outreach, specialist audiences, teaching, and my own understanding. The availability of both free and open-source visualization packages and free online access to a wide range of Earth Science data offer many options for anyone with a computer and internet access to make graphics that previoiusly took a dedicated team of specialists to create. Exciting times!  

One of my main goals with data visualization is to help convey scientific information to the public and decision-makers. However, I think it is also import to help people re-engage with the excitement, curiosity, and sense of wonder that comes from science and understanding how the natural world works.

I primarily work with Python, Blender, ParaView, and standard desktop software to make visualizations. I also have experimented a bit with 3D printing.
    
